## (5)(b) BASK with 4 bits per Symbol

> For the digital sequence shown in (a), draw the Binary Amplitude Shift Keying (BASK) encoded/modulated signal if each signal/symbol is represented by 4 bits. *(2 marks)*

---

**4-bit BASK (16-ASK):**

With 4 bits per symbol, we have **16 amplitude levels** (0-15).

Sequence grouped: `0100 1011 01xx`

| Symbol | Bits | Decimal | Amplitude |
|--------|------|---------|-----------|
| 1 | 0100 | 4 | 4/15 of max |
| 2 | 1011 | 11 | 11/15 of max |
| 3 | 01xx | (padded) | - |

> Each symbol's amplitude is proportional to its decimal value.

