## (5)(c) FSK Advantages and Disadvantages

> Describe advantages and disadvantages of Frequency Shift Keying (FSK) encoding. *(2 marks)*

---

**Advantages:**

- **Immune to amplitude noise** - information is in frequency, not amplitude
- **Simple to implement** - just switch between two oscillators
- **Good for noisy channels** - more robust than ASK

**Disadvantages:**

- **Bandwidth inefficient** - needs bandwidth for both frequencies
- **Lower data rate** - only 1 bit per symbol (binary FSK)
- **Complex receiver** - needs frequency discriminator

