## (5)(d) 16-QAM Constellation Diagram

> Draw the constellation diagram for 16-QAM (16-Quadratic Amplitude Modulation) encoding. *(4 marks)*

---

::qam16-constellation

**16-QAM:**

- 16 points arranged in a 4×4 grid
- Each point represents 4 bits
- Uses both **amplitude** and **phase**
- Points at corners have highest amplitude

