## (5)(f) Convolutional Codes vs Block Codes

> Compare Convolutional Codes to (linear) Block Codes and explain their use in the communication chain. *(4 marks)*

---

| Aspect | Block Codes | Convolutional Codes |
|--------|-------------|---------------------|
| **Input** | Fixed blocks (e.g., 4 bits) | Continuous stream |
| **Memory** | None (each block independent) | Has memory (shift register) |
| **Encoding** | Matrix multiplication | Shift register + XOR |
| **Decoding** | Syndrome lookup | Viterbi algorithm |
| **Latency** | Low (block-by-block) | Higher (sliding window) |
| **Example** | Hamming (7,4) | Rate 1/2, K=3 |

---

**Use in Communication Chain:**

1. **Block codes (e.g., Reed-Solomon)** - outer code, corrects burst errors
2. **Convolutional codes** - inner code, corrects random errors
3. **Interleaving** between them spreads burst errors

> **Turbo codes** and **LDPC** combine ideas from both for near-Shannon-limit performance.
